label flashback3: 
    #FLASHBACK SCHOOL / UNI
    scene school

    # Change to School animation CG


    nrt "It sounds so simple, said like that. In many ways, it is. You’ve been making it such a big deal in your head that you’ve almost forgotten that, for most of your life, everyone just kind of knew."
    nrt "Having a white brother at the same school made it easy enough for most people to connect the dots, give or take a few poorly phrased jokes about really taking after one parent more than the other."
    nrt "Besides that, the small Asian contingent at your mostly white primary and secondary schools had been almost entirely Indian and Pakistani."
    nrt "And that one half-Nepali girl who’d mocked you for not being able to handle a medium at Nando’s, then wilted in shame when she managed to get sunburnt in April. In England."
    nrt "And sure, you’d all been friends. Kinda. Hung out with them more than anyone else."
    nrt "But you’d never been close. How much of that was them being a different version of Asian, how much of it was none of them being adopted?"
    nrt "And how much of it was just because you’re kind of a loser who no one wants to make any more effort than necessary to hang out with."


    # nat_neutral_sideeye
    nth ne_sd "(I guess. Although I’m pretty sure it had a lot more to do with me being gay.)"

    nrt"Was it though? You were already the unpopular weird kid long before Kevin graciously let slip that you’re a lesbian. All that did was add another arrow to the quiver of all the kids who were gonna bully you anyway."
    nrt "Sure, a couple of the Asian delegation had been weird or outright homophobic to you about it, but most of them, like the rest of the school, just didn’t really give a shit."

    # nat_neutral
    nth ne "(That was… kind of the problem, to be honest.)"
    # nat_angry or annoyed, not sure which would work better
    nth an "(Like, I’m sorry if the core part of my identity matters to me.)"

    nrt "Did you expect them to give you a cookie? A special parade for being the first out and proud lesbian in your year?"

    # nat_neutral_sideeye
    nth ne_sd "(Would’ve been nice if someone had cared.)"

    nrt "Oh, are you blaming your family now? Have you not read enough horror stories of queer kids hiding themselves from their abusive parents to not be extremely grateful for your family’s acceptance?"

    # nat_sad_eyesclosed
    nth sa_ec "(No, I know. I do.)"
    # nat_annoyed
    nth an "(Hell, I know that Kev only outed me cause he didn’t even realise it was a big deal.)"
    # nat_neutral
    nth ne "(I know I should be grateful, and I guess I am.)"
    # nat_dejected_smile
    nth dj_s "(I wasn’t asking for them to put a big WE LOVE OUR GAY DAUGHTER bumper sticker on the car or anything but…)"
    # nat_neutral
    nth ne "(It would’ve been nice if they’d, like, been excited for me when I came out to them? Looked up some local queer youth groups? Taken me to Pride?)"

    nrt "Even if they had, would that have been enough for you, or would you have found something else to complain about?"

    # nat_dejected
    nth dj "(Knowing me? Probably.)"

    nrt "You were just bitter."

    # nat_annoyed
    nth an "(What, that the popular white girls got to come out as bi and get celebrated for their bravery, meanwhile their friends would scream if I glanced within a mile radius of them in the PE changing room?)"
    # nat_angry
    nth ag "(Yeah. I was bitter. Still am.)"

    nrt "And what does any of that have to do with not feeling connected to the other Asian girls at school?"

    # nat_dejected
    nth dj "(Well, they didn’t give a shit, right?)"
    # nat_angry
    nth ag "(Shocker, it’s kinda hard to form any real authentic connections when no one cares about the real and authentic parts of you.)"

    nrt "Did it ever occur to you that some of them might have been forced into the closet? That had you made more of an effort, you might have made yourself some genuine connections and helped out a friend in need?"

    # nat_sad
    nth sa "(I guess a couple of them did kinda have bi energy, looking back on it…)"

    nrt "Roads untravelled, hm? Too late to worry about that, it’s been nearly a decade since you’ve spoken with any of them. You probably wouldn’t have been able to help anyway."
    nrt "But that was how it was for eighteen years. The Chinese girl that everyone knew was basically white."
    nrt "Then for three of those years you got to be the Chinese lesbian that everyone knew didn’t get disowned for it because white Londoners couldn’t socially get away with beating their gay kids anymore."

    # Scene change to university CG (if it exists)

    nrt "It was only at uni, where you’d finally been away from Kevin, away from all of your family, where you finally encountered more Chinese people than the staff at Happy Garden."
    nrt "That’s when you and your surname became something you had to explain. Why your spice tolerance was so crap, why you couldn’t speak Cantonese or Mandarin, why you didn’t recognise any of the cultural references any of the other Chinese students made."

    # nat_neutral_sideeye
    nth ne_sd "(Not that I ever needed to explain anything to the Chinese-born students.)"

    nrt "Oh yeah. They knew. They could tell within a few seconds of speaking to you, and the sting of that rejection repeated enough that you stopped even bothering."

    # nat_neutral
    nth ne "(So who could really blame me when I just… stopped explaining. To anyone.)"
    # nat_neutral_smile
    nth ne_s "(Honestly, it felt like the best decision I ever made.)"

    nrt "It was great, wasn’t it? For a time. Sure, you held your breath any time your Extremely British Surname came up, any time a student or professor who’d only seen your full name in emails did a double take upon seeing you in the flesh."
    nrt "But no one ever called you on it. It seemed like they just didn’t know. Maybe you were a little mixed, maybe your parents had taken an English surname, it’s not like any of them knew any better, right?"

    # nat_surprised
    nth su "(I remember all the excuses and explanations I came up with and then I just… never needed to use any of them. No one ever asked.)"

    nrt "Even being gay wasn’t that big a deal at uni. Being gay and Chinese still made you a bit of an oddity, but that was just because the Beijing clique all kept to themselves."

    # nat_neutral_smile_sideeye
    nth ne_s_sd "(Maybe they were having secret sapphic orgies in each other’s dorms, it’s not like anyone would ever know.)"

    nrt "You’d started wearing rainbow pins, lesbian flags. No one called you slurs or anything. Maybe a few people had been a bit shittier to you than they would have otherwise been, but that might have just been your natural charisma at play."

    # nat_angry
    nth ag "(There were still a few creepy guys who didn’t get the hint, but that one feels pretty universal.)"

    nrt "Unfortunately so. On the other side of things, it seemed like practically every girl you met was “bi-ish,” which usually meant, “if Ciara dragged you out to a club night and got a couple of drinks into you and pushed you and some other girl in the same direction, you’d probably end up making out.”"

    # nat_neutral_smile
    nth ne_s "(Still way better than secondary school had ever been.)"

    nrt "You’d finally been able to be yourself. And it wasn’t enough, because you weren’t actually being yourself, were you?"
    nrt "You were a plaything for bi-curious white girls in a K-Pop phase who didn’t know any better. The only people who knew the real you were the housemates who saw your parents drop your stuff off."

    # nat_neutral_smile
    nth ne_s "(And the only one of them I ever really talked to was Ciara, and she didn’t really give a shit either way.)"

    nrt "So, that left your fellow Chinese-Brits. The forbidden fruit. The only people you truly hoped you might ever feel at home with, and yet the only people who could immediately identify you for what you really were."
    nrt "You’re not sure when that fact became so terrifying. Sure, there’s the obvious point that if your own people reject you, you’ll truly have nothing left, but it’s not like you ever reach out to them in the first place to be rejected."
    nrt "If you crave that community so much, why is Lillian the only other Chinese-Brit you’ve ever spoken to for more than a few seconds?"

    # nat_neutral_sideeye
    nth ne_sf "(Because she’s gorgeous and I’m gay?)"

    nrt "No. Because you had to. Because she was assigned to your group, and if not you’d have just admired her in fear and awe from afar."
    nrt "Even this connection, one of the few things that can make you feel whole, is something you fluked into and nearly ruined on multiple occasions."
    nrt "Like just now."
